---
import { Page, Block } from '../../components/DocPage.js';
import {
  AttrValue,
  AttrToggle,
  BehaviorProp,
  Each,
  EachKey,
  EachItems,
  EachTemplate,
  Event,
  EventListener,
  EventCapture,
  EventOnce,
  EventPassive,
  EventSignal,
  EventTarget,
  StoreRoot,
  StoreSet
} from '../../components/Links.js';
---

<Page title="Properties">
  <Block>
    <p>In Corset, <strong>properties</strong> are used to bind to aspects of an element, such as its attributes, text, and events.</p>
    <p>Corset includes both properties and <strong>shorthand properties</strong>, properties that combine multiple properties together.</p>
    <p>Corset also contains multi-binding properties; properties such as event and attr can be used to bind to multiple things.</p>
  </Block>

  <section>
    <h2>Element properties</h2>
    <p>These properties bind to the major parts of an element.</p>
    <Block>
      <dl>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/text/">text</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Set the text content of an element.</dd>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/class-toggle/">class-toggle</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Toggle classes on an element.</dd>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/attr/">attr</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Attribute shorthand for <AttrValue /> and <AttrToggle />.</dd>
        <dt><AttrValue /></dt>
        <dd>Longhand for setting the value of an attribute on an element.</dd>
        <dt><AttrToggle /></dt>
        <dd>Toggle boolean attributes on an element.</dd>
        <dt><Event /></dt>
        <dd>Add event listeners on an element.</dd>
        <dt><EventListener /></dt>
        <dd>Specifiers the listener for the event.</dd>
        <dt><EventCapture /></dt>
        <dd>Specifies if the listener should be called during the capture phase.</dd>
        <dt><EventOnce /></dt>
        <dd>Specifies that the listener should be called only once.</dd>
        <dt><EventPassive /></dt>
        <dd>Specifies that the listener will not call <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/preventDefault">preventDefault()</a>.</dd>
        <dt><EventSignal /></dt>
        <dd>Specifies an <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbortSignal">AbortSignal</a> that will remove the listener when aborted.</dd>
        <dt><EventTarget /></dt>
        <dd>Specifies the target of the event (if not the selected element).</dd>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/prop/">prop</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Set properties on the DOM element.</dd>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/data/">data</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Set dataset values on an element.</dd>
      </dl>
    </Block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Looping properties</h2>
    <p>These properties are used to define the behavior of an iterable (each).</p>

    <Block>
      <dl>
        <dt><Each /></dt>
        <dd>Shorthand property to define an each iteration.</dd>
        <dt><EachItems /></dt>
        <dd>Set the items (such an array) to iterate on.</dd>
        <dt><EachTemplate /></dt>
        <dd>Sets the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/template">&lt;template&gt;</a> element to use for each item in the iterable.</dd>
        <dt><EachKey /></dt>
        <dd>Defines a key to use to identify items in the iterable.</dd> 
      </dl>
    </Block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Other properties</h2>
    <p>These properties attach behavior to elements when matched.</p>
    <Block>
      <dl>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/attach-template/">attach-template</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Replace the children of an element with a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/template">&lt;template&gt;</a>.</dd>
        <dt><BehaviorProp /></dt>
        <dd>Mount behaviors to an element.</dd>
        <dt><StoreRoot /></dt>
        <dd>Creates a <em>store</em> where state can be shared.</dd>
        <dt><StoreSet /></dt>
        <dd>Sets a (keyed) value in a store.</dd>
        <dt>
          <a href="properties/custom-properties/">custom properties</a>
        </dt>
        <dd>Custom properties, like in CSS, use a <code>--dashed</code> syntax.</dd>
      </dl>
    </Block>
  </section>
</Page>